         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 6/9/83. ¶ Mons. E. A. Pesoli, ¶ Acting Consul for France. ¶ Sir....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.09.06</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To E. Pesoli</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Carton no. 17, Melbourne, consulat, Serie A, Centre des Archives Diplomatiques, Nantes.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">6/9/83.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Mons. E. A. Pesoli,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Acting Consul for France.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Of the seeds, desired by Mons. Carrière, the Gov. Inspector of Forests in Paris, only <name key="Eucalyptus%20rostrata">Eucalyptus rostrata</name>, E. obliqua and <name key="Acacia%20pycnantha">Acacia pycnantha</name> can at this moment be supplied; but as E. tereticornis and E. rostrata are only varieties of one species, I have doubled the quantity of the seeds of the latter for your sending, especially as this tree is one of the most valuable of all Eucalypts. This you will see on reference to my "descriptive Atlas of the Eucalypts"<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B79.13.11 and subsequent parts.</p>
               </note> and to the volume "select plants for industrial culture and naturalisation".<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B81.13.10.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It seems to me, that M. Carrière, (with whose name I am familiar since many years as that of an author of a most valuable work on Coniferae<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Carrière (1855).</p>
               </note>), will be in a better position to judge, which particular species of Eucalyptus are most eligible for his cultures in any part of South France or Algeria, after this distinguished Officer has obtained the works alluded to.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ready at any time, to render to the Great Government, which you so well represent, any services, and continuing the interest in the "reboisements"<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>reafforestations.</p>
               </note> which I took since the last 25 years, I remain, dear Consul, your very regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Acacia%20pycnantha">Acacia pycnantha</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20obliqua">Eucalyptus obliqua</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20rostrata">Eucalyptus rostrata</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20tereticornis">Eucalyptus tereticornis</name>
            </p>
         </div>
